&lt;h1 id="write-professionally"&gt;Write professionally&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Read over your compositions, and wherever you meet with a passage which you think is particularly fine, strike it out.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samuel_Johnson"&gt;Samuel Johnson&lt;/a&gt;, quoted in “ &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Life_of_Samuel_Johnson"&gt;The Life of Samuel Johnson&lt;/a&gt; “, by &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Boswell"&gt;James Boswell&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This advice is mainly for first-time authors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A journal article is going to be a permanent record of your work; thus it is important that these articles are as professionally written as possible, so as not to cause embarrassment several years from now.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>